<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,402,708]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,402,428]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tube from pale pink to salmon, with prominent longitudinal ridge, forming crest, lacking peristomes or alveoli. Opercular peduncle with wide wings. Operculum with up to five successive calcareous plates, becoming progressively smaller toward apex (
<figureCitation box="[772,881,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="51.[151,255,1902,1926]" captionTargetBox="[263,1320,187,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-62@51.[228,1358,184,1878]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 13. A: Spirobranchus latiscapus, from Hawaii. A, operculum, lateral view. B–C: Spirobranchus spinosus, from California, USNM 17109, holotype. B–C, operculum, aboral and lateral views. D: Vermiliopsis infundibulum/glandigera complex, from Baja California Sur, UANL 365. D, operculum, lateral view. (Fig. A, redrawn from Bailey-Brock, 1972)." pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Collar with “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1818" box="[1052,1223,482,507]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Spirobranchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1052,1223,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Spirobranchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” chaetae coarsely serrated in subapical section.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,402,708]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,301,562,588]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Habitat.</emphasis>
Depth: 
<quantity box="[399,522,562,588]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.35" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="317.5" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="35.0">
35– 
<specimenCount box="[443,522,562,588]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">600 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. On gastropod shells of 
<taxonomicName box="[814,1024,562,587]" class="Gastropoda" family="Xenophoridae" genus="Xenophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[814,1024,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Xenophora tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on precious pink coral 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dana" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Anthozoa" family="Coralliidae" genus="Corallium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="secundum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Corallium secundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and on solitary coral 
<emphasis box="[523,643,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Cyatheras</emphasis>
sp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
